  "texts": [
    "The researchers suggested a novel 3D model called voxel graph that was both compact and expressive for creating geometries in place of producing dense 3D voxels.",
    "The pipeline was trained using an adversarial framework, and their generator was a cross-modal graph neural network that connected the input programed graph and the output voxel graph via a pointer mechanism.",
    "A user study was used to evaluate the created designs qualitatively, and three metrics-quality, diversity, and connectivity accuracy-were used to evaluate them quantitatively.",
    "The researchers demonstrated that the established model produced 3D volumetric designs that were realistic and performed better than baselines and earlier techniques.",
    "Visual prediction of signalsUsing machine learning techniques, Li et al. [85] offered a preliminary solution for the use case of monitoring the surveillance system in which sporadic unexpected events take place."
